<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,777,1012]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,819,845]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body vermiform; scapular tubercles and setae present, scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[1172,1196,820,845]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">sc</emphasis>
) directed anteriorly, anterior shield lobe absent; opsithosoma with standard setae, dorsoventral annuli subequal; legs with usual setae, empodium entire.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,777,1012]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
This genus consists of 299 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[654,896,945,971]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[758,814,945,970]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Only 18 species have been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
